From Craig Eid Subject Candlestick Park experience long I've been a Giants season ticket holder for years and never really complained about the old ballyard Sure it's been cold the food lines were long and the hired hands were surly but this was all part of the Giants Or so I I went to Tuesday's game Giants over the Marlins and the 'Stick was a much different Nothing short of a dome will eliminate the wind but everything is a lot The lines are a lot shorter the bathrooms are CLEAN and have running water and the hired hands were very The new foghorn lights up and blows after each homerun and the wooden fence are very nice as are the new The bleachers start right at the top of the fence and give a great view and they've got beer stands at the bottome of the The only complaint is that the electronic old fashioned scoreboard looks electronic could be These things should have been done a long time ago but it took a real businessman ex Safeway President Peter Magowan to figure it Just like he used to tell his checkers If the customers don't come back I don't need as many checkers This isn't a knock on Bob Lurie he was a competent businessman but he didn't deal much with the general I'll give an example of how the level of service has The onion dispenser jammed as I was using An attendant came over apoligized for the problem and proceeded to fix the After he was done he cleaned the machine and said he was glad to be able to In the old days there was no attendant and the folks at the concession stands would say Go to the stand feet away they might be able to help All in all it was a fun day Craig Eid e mail address